A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Public Safety – Missing Person Reports – Collection and Publication
3 FOR the purpose of requiring the Department of State Police to compile and report on its
4 website certain information on missing person reports in the State; requiring a local
5 law enforcement agency to provide certain information on missing person reports to
6 the Department of State Police as required by the Department of State Police;
7 requiring the Department of State Police to adopt procedures for the collection of
8 information from local law enforcement agencies; and generally relating to missing
9 person cases.
10 BY adding to
11 Article – Public Safety
12 Section 3–609
13 Annotated Code of Maryland
14 (2022 Replacement Volume and 2024 Supplement)
15 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
16 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
17 Article – Public Safety
18 3–609.
19 (A) THE DEPARTMENT OF STATE POLICE SHALL COLLECT AND PUBLISH ON
20 ITS WEBSITE INFORMATION ON MISSING PERSON REPORTS IN THE STATE.
21 (B) THE INFORMATION PUBLISHED UNDER SUBSECTION (A) OF THIS
22 SECTION SHALL:
