5 (C) ON OR BEFORE DECEMBER 31 EACH YEAR, THE DEPARTMENT OF
6 STATE POLICE SHALL PUBLISH ON ITS WEBSITE A SUMMARY OF ALL INFORMATION
7 ON MISSING PERSON REPORTS REQUIRED UNDER THIS SECTION FOR THE
8 PRECEDING CALENDAR YEAR.
9 (D) EACH LOCAL LAW ENFORCEMENT AGENCY SHALL PROVIDE THE
10 DEPARTMENT OF STATE POLICE WITH INFORMATION REGARDING ANY MISSING
11 PERSON WITHIN THE JURISDICTION OF THE AGENCY AS REQUIRED BY THE
12 DEPARTMENT OF STATE POLICE.
13 (E) THE DEPARTMENT OF STATE POLICE SHALL ADOPT PROCEDURES
14 NECESSARY FOR THE COLLECTION OF INFORMATION PROVIDED BY LOCAL LAW
15 ENFORCEMENT AGENCIES AS REQUIRED UNDER SUBSECTION (D) OF THIS SECTION.
16 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
17 1, 2026.

